ly during the Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD ). (iii) traced back to other minority ethnic groups in ancient northwestern China.","Mandarin form of the Chinese surname 邸, meaning ‘official residence’ in Chinese: (i) from placename Di (邸), the name of a county (unidentified location). (ii) said to be borne by some descendants of Kujula Kadphises (called 丘就郤 or 邸就郤 in Chinese, 30–<i>c.</i> 80  AD ), founder of the Kushan Empire (one branch of the Yuezhi people originating from western China) located in Central Asia during the Eastern Han dynasty (25–220  AD )."],"variants":[{"name":"Chi","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Young, Dong, Yun, Cheng, Jae, Yong, Cheng Chung, Chi, Chun, Duk, Fang, Feng.  Korean Chung, Chong, Jae Hong, Moon, Myong, Pong, Shen, Yoo, Byung, Chang, Chol, Chong Hun.  Southeast Asian Phi, Hung, Ly, Tu, Denh, Do Van, Duong, Hao, Kieu, Mui, Nga, Phat.","Chinese: Mandarin and Cantonese form of the surname 池, meaning ‘moat’ in ancient Chinese: (i) acquired as a surname by people who lived beside a moat. (ii) from Chi (池), said to be the name of an ancient state (of unknown location and period). (iii) from the personal name Chi (池), personal name of a son of an official in the state of Qin during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ).","Chinese: Mandarin and Cantonese form of the surname 遲, meaning ‘late’ in Chinese: (i) borne by descendants of Chi Ren (遲任), a person who lived during the Shang dynasty (1600–1046  BC ). (ii) shortened form of the Chinese compound surname Yu-Chi (尉遲), originally the name of a tribe from the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China. (iii) from the second element of the personal name Zi Chi (子遲), style name of Fan Xu, a student of Confucius (551–479  BC )."]}]},{"name":"Baschi","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Indian and Bangladeshi: Barendra Brahmin habitational name from Bagcha, a village near Barackpore in West Bengal."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Ugolino","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Alberto, Aldo, Amerigo, Angelo, Arrigo, Constantino, Corrado, Enrico, Gino, Grazia, Marco, Marino, Olinto, Piero, Valeriano.","Italian (Tuscany): patronymic or plural form of the personal name <i>Ugolino</i>, a name of ancient Germanic origin, which was particularly popular in the medieval period. It is generally considered to be a pet form of <i>Ugo</i> (equivalent of   Hugo  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Hugo","meanings":["Latinized form of   Hugh  , used throughout the Middle Ages in official documents, and now enjoying a revival as a given name."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Ugolino Di Baschi was born about 1170, in Baschi, Terni, Umbria, Italy, his father, Neri Di Baschi, was 32 and his mother, Mrs Neri Di Baschi, was 24. He had at least 1 son with Mrs Ugolino Di Baschi."},"et":{"ABT 1170–":"umbes 1170–Surnud","1170–Male":"1170–Surnud","1178–Female":"1178–Surnud","1200–1225":"1200–1225","1140–Male":"1140–Surnud","1148–Female":"1148–Surnud","1148":"1148","1225":"1225","1200":"1200","1178":"1178","about 1200":"umbes 1200","1140":"1140","ABT 1170":"umbes 1170","1170":"1170","BASCHI,, IT":"Baschi, Terni, Umbria, Itaalia","BASCHI, , IT":"Baschi, Terni, Umbria, Itaalia"},"fi":{"ABT 1170–":"noin 1170–Kuollut","1170–Male":"1170–Kuollut","1178–Female":"1178–Kuollut","1200–1225":"1200–1225","1140–Male":"1140–Kuollut","1148–Female":"1148–Kuollut","1148":"1148","1225":"1225","1200":"1200","1178":"1178","about 1200":"noin 1200","1140":"1140","ABT 1170":"noin 1170","1170":"1170","BASCHI,, IT":"Baschi, Terni, Umbria, Italia","BASCHI, , IT":"Baschi, Terni, Umbria, Italia"},"fr":{"ABT 1170–":"environ 1170–Décédé","1170–Male":"1170–Décédé","1178–Female":"1178–Décédée","1200–1225":"1200–1225","1140–Male":"1140–Décédé","1148–Female":"1148–Décédée","1148":"1148","1225":"1225","1200":"1200","1178":"1178","about 12